text: Buchanan County is a county located in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 20,565. Its county seat is Independence. The county was founded on December 21, 1837 and was named in honor of Senator James Buchanan, the 15th President of the United States. == References == Category:1837 establishments in Wisconsin Territory Category:Iowa counties
title: Buchanan County, Iowa
